In no case other than Libby's does the indictment contend that one of the government employees provided the name to reporters. Of course, the ``vice president of the United States'' is Dick Cheney, for whom Libby worked as chief of staff. Libby discussed Plame's employment at the CIA with Fleischer, noting ``that such information was not widely known,'' the indictment said. This person, identified as ``Official A,'' also spoke about Plame's job and identity with columnist Robert Novak a few days before Novak's column appeared. 